<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4803&amp;p=20308#p20308</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4803&amp;p=20308#p20308"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Classic Shell 4.2.3 release candidate]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4803&amp;p=20308#p20308"><![CDATA[
<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline">Other changes and detailed change log:</span></strong> <br /><br />● The Metro skin in Classic styles can have glass. It can be toggled from the Skin tab when the Metro skin is selected <br />● You can right-click on a highlighted program and select &quot;Remove highlight&quot; <br />● The Start Menu has the ability now to move itself, for example, when the Windows 8/8.1 and Windows 10 touch keyboard pops up in the docked state or when the resolution changes (like when you exit a fullscreen game with the Win key) <br />● <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?f=4&amp;t=4750#p20000" class="postlink">Known issues from Classic Shell 4.2.2 beta</a> are fixed. <br /><br />Thanks to <em>juniper7 </em>for reporting issues with skins and for creating awesome skins. <br /><br /><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline">Known issues in Classic Shell 4.2.3: (Fixed in Classic Shell 4.2.4)<br /></span></strong>● On Windows 10, the taskbar may disappear (Explorer crashes) when you click the Start button. See this post (<!-- l --><a class="postlink-local" href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=4822">viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=4822</a><!-- l -->) for a patch that corrects it for now before the next version is released. <br />● On Windows 10, the &quot;Tasks&quot; section of jumplists for some programs may not appear although &quot;Recent&quot; shows up. <br />● On Windows 10, if your user account does not have a password, using &quot;Switch user&quot; from the Start Menu will automatically log you in again <br />● On Windows 10, the Classic Start Menu may open with a delay when &quot;Show recent Metro apps&quot; setting is enabled <br />● On Windows 10, the 'Run' item does not work for users who have their taskbar at the top or at the side <br />● On Windows 10, dragging to the Start button doesn't always open the *Classic* Start Menu as it should <br />● On Windows 10, the Start Menu causes Explorer to become unresponsive if a user account picture is not set <br />● On Windows 10, Classic Explorer Settings will not show any options for Navigation pane style in Basic Settings mode <br />● In Classic styles of the menu, the PC Settings command does not work if the item has a split button or has sub-items <br /><br />Classic Shell 4.2.3 runs on Windows 7, Windows 8, Windows 8.1 and Windows 10. <br /><br />If you aren't sure which Start Menu to go with, or whether or not you still need a better Start Menu like Classic Shell, <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2399" class="postlink"><strong>here's a feature comparison</strong></a>:<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Sun Jul 26, 2015 10:16 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
